Day 1:

VPCs: Learn about Amazon Virtual Private Cloud (VPC), a logically isolated virtual network within the AWS Cloud, and how to use it to launch AWS resources. Read the AWS VPC User Guide.
Link: https://docs.aws.amazon.com/vpc/latest/userguide/what-is-amazon-vpc.html
VPC Tutorial: Watch the "AWS VPC Tutorial" video to get hands-on experience with creating and configuring a VPC.
Link: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SCo-4OG0zLU
Day 2:

Subnets: Learn about subnets, a range of IP addresses in your VPC, and how to use them to launch resources in your VPC. Read the AWS VPC Subnets User Guide.
Link: https://docs.aws.amazon.com/vpc/latest/userguide/VPC_Subnets.html
Subnets Tutorial: Watch the "AWS VPC Subnets Tutorial" video to get hands-on experience with creating and configuring subnets.
Link: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=L5fR5cKgHzY
Day 3:

Route Tables: Learn about route tables, a set of rules used to determine where network traffic is directed in your VPC. Read the AWS VPC Route Tables User Guide.
Link: https://docs.aws.amazon.com/vpc/latest/userguide/VPC_Route_Tables.html
Route Tables Tutorial: Watch the "AWS VPC Route Tables Tutorial" video to get hands-on experience with creating and configuring route tables.
Link: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xEiRvoJfV9E
Day 4:

NAT Gateways: Learn about Network Address Translation (NAT) gateways, a highly available AWS managed service that makes it easy to connect resources in a private subnet to the internet. Read the AWS NAT Gateway User Guide.
Link: https://docs.aws.amazon.com/vpc/latest/userguide/vpc-nat-gateway.html
NAT Gateways Tutorial: Watch the "AWS NAT Gateway Tutorial" video to get hands-on experience with creating and configuring NAT gateways.
Link: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZGpR0eemd0s
Day 5:

Internet Gateways: Learn about internet gateways, a horizontally scalable, redundant, and highly available VPC component that allows communication between instances in your VPC and the internet. Read the AWS Internet Gateway User Guide.
Link: https://docs.aws.amazon.com/vpc/latest/userguide/VPC_Internet_Gateway.html
Internet Gateways Tutorial: Watch the "AWS Internet Gateway Tutorial" video to get hands-on experience with creating and configuring internet gateways.
Link: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KftZPc3wAHk
Day 6:

VPNs: Learn about AWS Virtual Private Network (VPN), a secure and reliable way to connect your on-premises network or remote site to your AWS VPC. Read the AWS VPN User Guide.
Link: https://docs.aws.amazon.com/vpn/latest/s2svpn/Welcome.html
VPN Tutorial: Watch the "AWS VPN Tutorial" video to get hands-on experience with creating and configuring a VPN connection.
Link: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ay8oKs3s9XQ
Day 7:

Direct Connect: Learn about AWS Direct Connect, a dedicated network connection from your premises to AWS that can reduce your network costs, increase bandwidth throughput, and provide a more consistent network experience. Read